### V.8 — IMPL Resolution: match lines ARE the VRF-rolled tickets (USER sign-off 2026-06-20; supersedes the §E.1/§V deterministic buy-time signature)

**Status: AUTHORITATIVE. Supersedes the deterministic buy-time `packedTraitsFoil` signature roll wherever §E.1/§V.1 describe it, and the `buyDay` no-look-back floor of §V.2.** The two channels of §V.7 (the 16 VRF jackpot entries + the 4 deterministic match lines) are UNIFIED into ONE VRF roll: the 16 boosted entries ARE the 4 four-quadrant match lines (16 = 4 tickets × 4 quadrants). There is no separate deterministic signature.

- **Buy writes no lines.** `_buyFoilPack` freezes ONLY `multBps` into `foilRecord[lvl][buyer]` (`multBps ≥ 20000`, so the slot is non-zero and its presence IS the one-per-cycle cap). The signature lanes `[0-127]` and the line-day field stay zero. No live RNG, no line, no `packedTraitsFoil` call at buy.
- **The drain rolls the lines from the day's VRF word.** The relocated drain (see §V.9) rolls 4 four-quadrant boosted tuples per buyer off `keccak(entropy, buyer, lvl, FOIL_SEED_TAG, i)` (`entropy` = the processing word; the buyer cannot choose it). Each tuple's 4 traits file into the jackpot buckets `traitBurnTicket[lvl]` AND the 4 tuples stamp into `foilRecord` as `sig0..sig3` via `_foilStampRoll`, alongside `lineDay` = the roll day (`_simulatedDayIndex()`, the same domain as the `dailyFoilDraw` key). One SLOAD (multBps) + one SSTORE (sigs+lineDay) per buyer on top of the bucket writes.
- **No-look-back is `day > lineDay`** (replaces `day > buyDay`): a pack matches only draws strictly AFTER its lines were rolled — future, unseen words. The claim ALSO requires `lineDay != 0` (rolled), which gates out any claim against an un-rolled record (whose zero sigs would spuriously match a zero winning quadrant). The implicit upper bound (cycle-level match of §V.1) is unchanged.
- **SEC-01 strengthens.** The line is now VRF (not merely pre-committed deterministic) AND committed before every matched draw — fully unsteerable on both the symbol and the color. The hero touches at most one quadrant of the *winning* set; the line is independent VRF.
- **No rebalance.** Match odds stay binomial(4 lines, 1/64/quadrant): the *winning* set is flat-uniform (`getRandomTraits`), so `P(line[q] == win[q]) = Σ_t P(line=t)·(1/64) = 1/64` for ANY line distribution — boosting the line is M-invariant for matching. The match-odds calibration holds verbatim (the per-tier faces are a separate lever, set in §E.5/§E.7). The boost still shapes only the jackpot-bucket flavor (rare colors / gold), exactly as before.
- **Edit-surface delta from §V.5:** `foilRecord` layout `[168-191]` is `lineDay` (was `buyDay`); the buy drops the sig roll + `_currentMintDay`; `_foilSigFor` returns `lineDay`; new `_foilStampRoll` (storage) writes sigs+lineDay preserving multBps; `_FOIL_BUYDAY_*` → `_FOIL_LINEDAY_*` (+ a `_FOIL_SIGS_MASK`). `packedTraitsFoil` survives as the documented/tested 4-lane producer but is no longer called by the buy.

### V.9 — IMPL Resolution: foil drain relocated to the foil module (EIP-170; USER sign-off 2026-06-20)

**Status: AUTHORITATIVE. Resolves the CATASTROPHIC EIP-170 overflow the §V.5-as-built incurred (`DegenerusGameMintModule` = 26,012 B, 1,436 B over the 24,576 limit).** The foil-drain spine moves OUT of `DegenerusGameMintModule` (near-full) and INTO `DegenerusGameFoilPackModule` (~19 KB headroom):

- **MintModule reverts to its pre-foil normal-ticket path verbatim:** `_raritySymbolBatch` (drop the `multBps` param + the `foilCut` hoist + the `foilTrait` ternary), `_processOneTicketEntry` (drop the bookkeeping reorder), and the `processFutureTicketBatch` call site all restore to the committed-HEAD form. The normal mint/ticket path is therefore BYTE-IDENTICAL to the pre-foil baseline (stronger than the prior `multBps==0` equivalence argument). The local `_processFoilDrain` is deleted.
- **MintModule keeps a thin hook:** `processTicketBatch`, once the normal queue drains, calls `_drainFoil(lvl, rk, room, entropy)` which `delegatecall`s `DegenerusGameFoilPackModule.processFoilDrain` (runs in the Game's storage context; `address(this)==GAME` guard; nested-delegatecall pattern already used by `_payFoilEth`→lootbox). The both-queues readiness gate (AdvanceModule, `foilCursor < foilTicketQueue.length`) is UNCHANGED.
- **FoilPackModule gains** `processFoilDrain` (external, delegatecall-only) + `_processFoilDrain` (budget loop, `foilCursor`, 35-unit-per-buyer charge, defer-whole-buyer-no-brick — same guard discipline as before) + `_resolveFoilBuyer` (the roll + a bucket-write assembly mirroring the mint module's, re-zeroing shared scratch per buyer). `IDegenerusGameFoilPackModule` gains the `processFoilDrain` selector; MintModule imports it.
- **EIP-170 (Plan 04):** re-measure ALL of Game / Mint / Jackpot / Foil / Advance; assert each `< 24,576 B`. The relocation must bring MintModule back under with margin; the foil module absorbs the moved code well within its headroom.

### V.10 — IMPL Resolution: match payout is a Degenerette box-spin; WWXRP worthless (USER sign-off 2026-06-20; supersedes the §E.5 direct-pay schedule — see the rewritten §E.5/§E.7)

**Status: AUTHORITATIVE.** The match payout is NOT a direct faces→value transfer; the tier `faces {7,65,1000}` are the STAKE into one existing Degenerette box-spin (per-N EV-flat, so boosted foil gold cannot tilt EV — the prior "MUST NOT route through Degenerette" rationale was wrong). The matched four-quadrant line `sel` is the spin's player ticket (item c). Two disjoint keccak lanes off the retained daily word: `FOIL_CCY_TAG` (the 40 ETH / 40 FLIP / 20 WWXRP currency split) and `FOIL_SPIN_TAG` (the spin seed); there is no magnitude lane. **WWXRP (20%) is worthless BY DESIGN** — the UI animates the currency-independent spin and reveals the currency only afterward ("a big win… in worthless WWXRP"), so all realized value comes from the ETH + FLIP lanes. Calibration (closed-form, §E.7): F ≈ 2.63 face-EV/pack/30d; the value-bearing lanes net **ETH ≈ 1.05 + FLIP ≈ 1.0 ≈ 2 tickets** (ETH runs ~5% hot from its top-bucket ROI bonus). ETH lane is solvency-capped (3-tier split + 10%-of-`futurePrizePool` clamp + lootbox spill); FLIP/WWXRP are mints. **A long level paying a foil holder more than the ~30-day calibration is an INTENDED game mechanic (USER 2026-06-20), not a leak** — the focused value-conservation audit returned `gate_safe = true` / zero confirmed leaks, with the whole-cycle eligibility window (no on-chain day cap) as the locked, by-design behavior. Inherited box-spin sub-features (S=9 whale halfpass, s≥7 ETH DGNRS, ETH recirc) apply to foil wins by design.

### V.11 — IMPL Resolution: "buy a foil pack" secondary quest on the first purchase day (USER sign-off 2026-06-20)

**Status: AUTHORITATIVE.** The foil-pack mechanics are UNCHANGED — foil tickets are purchasable any time, route to the same level as normal tickets, and roll their traits via the existing VRF drain; the pack is a normal purchase plus the match-bet lane and the boosted traits. The ONLY add is a quest:
- **`QUEST_TYPE_FOIL = 4`** repurposes the retired `QUEST_TYPE_RESERVED` (value 4; `QUEST_TYPE_COUNT` stays 10). It is excluded from the random slot-1 pool (`_bonusQuestType`), so it only ever lands when forced — exactly like `MINT_FLIP`. Count-based: `_progressUnit = 1`, `QUEST_FOIL_TARGET = 1` (one pack completes).
- **Forced onto slot 1 (secondary) only on the first purchase day of a level** — the day after the final jackpot, when the next level's tickets become purchasable. `rollDailyQuest` gains `forceFoil`; `AdvanceModule.rngGate` passes `forceFoil = phaseTransitionActive && gapDays == 0`. This is the existing-state signal (`phaseTransitionActive` is set at `_endPhase` and still true at the roll, which runs before the transition completes), so **no new storage / no layout change** — directly symmetric to the first-jackpot-day `forceMintFlip = lastPurchaseDay`. The two forces are mutually exclusive (opposite cycle ends); `forceFoil` takes precedence.
- **`handleFoilPack(player)`** (DegenerusQuests, `onlyGame`) mirrors `handleDecimator`: secondary-gated (requires the day's primary completed), one pack meets target, self-credits the FLIP reward via `creditFlip`; no level-quest leg (FOIL is never a level-quest type). `buyFoilPack` calls it as its final step after all buy state is written (CEI).
- Edit surface: `DegenerusQuests.sol`, `IDegenerusQuests.sol` (rollDailyQuest +`forceFoil`, +`handleFoilPack`), `DegenerusGameAdvanceModule.sol` (the rngGate arg), `DegenerusGameFoilPackModule.sol` (the buy hook). No storage slot added/moved/retyped anywhere.

